---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout title="Installation | CodeFi Docs">
  <div slot="header">
    <div class="text-neon-green font-mono text-sm mb-2">/ GETTING STARTED</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white">Installation</h1>
  </div>

  <h2>System Requirements</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Node.js:</strong> v18.0.0 or higher.</li>
    <li><strong>Python:</strong> v3.8+ (required for the <code>pygame</code> audio engine).</li>
    <li><strong>yt-dlp:</strong> Required for YouTube streaming features.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Global Install</h2>
  <p>The easiest way to get CodeFi is via the npm registry:</p>
  <pre><code>npm install -g @felizz23/codefi</code></pre>

  <h2>Post-Installation check</h2>
  <p>
    After installing, it is highly recommended to run the diagnostic tool to ensure all native dependencies are correctly configured:
  </p>
  <pre><code>codefi doctor</code></pre>

  <h2>Platform Specifics</h2>
  
  <h3>Windows</h3>
  <p>If you encounter issues with audio playback, ensure that the Microsoft C++ Redistributables are installed as they are required by <code>pygame</code>.</p>

  <h3>macOS / Linux</h3>
  <p>Most systems come with Python pre-installed. You may need to install <code>ffmpeg</code> for high-quality audio extraction from YouTube.</p>
</DocsLayout>
